name: ˈd͡ʒɛtɑ
description:
Jetta the border collie who I was dog sitting back in October, 2019. She was supposed to be a rescuer dog but got dismissed for being too gentle of a soul. A rescue rescuer, a loving creature, the infamous trash bags shedder. The one to set and cross borders and boundaries. Previously posted 'Love Is' bird feeder was photographed on the same day, during the same walk.

Picture taken with FujiFilm Digital Q1, a digital camera released in 2003 with 7Mb built-in storage, making the experience of using it very close to film photography. 

Resolution: 640x480

October, 2019
St. Petersburg, Russia
